Neocortex:

	Hughlings Jackson's clinical observations relate to three fundamental properties of the neocortex. 
		-1) the neocortex contains topographic maps
		-2) the parts of these maps which are used the most have the largest representations
		-3) the neocortex has a key role in the genesis of epilepsy.

	-The cortical circuitry is highly plastic in that 
	-it can change its functional organization in response to experience, and it is crucial for memory formation and storage.

	-price of this cortical plasticity is the risk of the wildly uncontrolled oscillations in neural activity that occur in epilepsy.

	-mnoho pokusu s motor-cortex, pri stimulaci slabymi elektrickymi pulzy se hybou svaly => slozite topograficke mapy pro ruzne svaly
	-opice: piti z male studny (sikovnost) a piti z velke studny (pohoda)
		-sikovne opice mely o hodne vetsi kortikalni reprezentaci pro prsty nez ty druhe
		-je to videt i u lidi kteri hraji na strunny nastroj nebo u slepcu - Brailovo pismo 
		-lepsi a presnejsi kontrola = vetsi reprezentace v kortexu

	
	
	
